ISTANBUL, Nov. 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkish authorities in Turkey's biggest city Istanbul have arrested a man considered a suspect in the investigation of the assassination of Haitian President Jovenel Moise, local media reported on Tuesday. The Hurriyet Daily News said court officials issued 40-day temporary custody for Samir Handal, who was wanted on an Interpol notice, upon the request of the Turkish Justice Ministry. Handal was detained at Istanbul Airport by the airport police on Monday, as he was flying in transit from the United States to Jordan, the daily said. According to the report, the suspect has been put in the Maltepe Prison on the Asian side of the city. Moise was shot dead at his residence during a raid conducted by a group of gunmen in July. Enditem